# Web Service First

Unless the user explicitly asks about GAS, Apps Script, spreadsheet scripts, or a specific `.gs` file, assume requests in this project are about the web service.

## Default Interpretation

- Start investigations from the web service code, runtime logs, deployment/configuration, API routes, scheduled jobs, and email/notification pipeline.
- Do not use currently open `.gs` files as evidence that the task is about GAS.
- If the target is ambiguous, ask whether the user means the web service or GAS before editing.

## GAS Boundary

- Only inspect or modify GAS/Apps Script files when the user explicitly names GAS, Apps Script, spreadsheet automation, or a `.gs` file.
- If GAS looks related but was not requested, mention it as a possible separate area instead of editing it.
